WEBVTT

00:02.044 --> 00:04.713
♪ This Strange Effect playing ♪

00:14.223 --> 00:19.478
‐ ♪ You've got this strange effect on me ♪

00:20.103 --> 00:22.022
♪ And I like it ♪

00:24.316 --> 00:29.530
♪ You've got this strange effect on me ♪

00:30.614 --> 00:32.449
♪ And I like it ♪

00:34.993 --> 00:39.373
♪ You make my world seem right ♪

00:40.165 --> 00:45.963
♪ You make my darkness bright, oh, yes ♪

00:45.963 --> 00:50.425
♪ You've got this strange effect on me ♪

00:51.677 --> 00:53.637
♪ And I like it ♪

00:56.974 --> 00:59.059
♪ And I like it ♪

01:02.229 --> 01:04.106
♪ And I like it ♪

01:17.119 --> 01:18.829
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

01:38.891 --> 01:39.933
[birds chirping]

01:41.685 --> 01:42.811
♪ mid‐tempo music playing ♪

01:52.696 --> 01:54.448
NAPOLEON: I'm actually
really looking forward to this.

01:55.157 --> 02:00.454
This place has won
two global wellness awards,

02:00.454 --> 02:02.873
mental wellness and social impact.

02:03.248 --> 02:06.585
Though, the latter might have been,
uh, an honorable mention.

02:06.585 --> 02:08.962
The fact is, this woman is giving us

02:08.962 --> 02:10.380
a massive price break.

02:12.424 --> 02:14.551
What a‐‐ what a socially
progressive thing to do.

02:14.551 --> 02:17.554
To put healing people ahead
of the profit motive.

02:18.222 --> 02:20.807
I mean, to‐‐ I think some
of these other folks here

02:21.683 --> 02:23.560
are paying‐‐ paying thousands of dollars.

02:24.311 --> 02:26.146
[sings] ♪ We got the golden ticket ♪

02:28.273 --> 02:30.484
I actually feel myself
getting lighter as I get nearer.

02:31.818 --> 02:33.654
It's going to be a good thing.
Don't you think so, honey?

02:34.905 --> 02:37.783
‐ I do.
‐ Yeah. How you doing, Zoe? Zoe!

02:39.117 --> 02:40.202
‐ Yeah.

02:40.202 --> 02:41.578
NAPOLEON: How you doing back there?

02:41.578 --> 02:44.748
‐ Oh, never better, Dad.
Just looking forward.

02:44.748 --> 02:46.458
‐ It's going to be great.

02:51.505 --> 02:53.257
[seagulls calling]
JESSICA: Hey guys, it's Jess.

02:53.257 --> 02:54.216
So, we're headed

02:54.216 --> 02:57.177
to a transformation retreat
called Tranquillum.

02:57.177 --> 02:59.596
I would tag them for you,
but they're not on social.

02:59.596 --> 03:01.765
It's like super mysterious.

03:02.850 --> 03:04.601
Anyway, we're gonna spend 10 days

03:04.601 --> 03:08.814
doing meditation,
yoga, healthy eating,

03:08.814 --> 03:10.816
and spending some quality time
with my man‐‐

03:12.609 --> 03:14.027
Damn it, Ben, did you do that on purpose?

03:14.027 --> 03:16.321
‐ It's this road. It's beating
the shit out of my car.

03:16.321 --> 03:18.615
‐ Now I have to record
the whole thing again.

03:19.867 --> 03:22.536
‐ You don't have to.
‐ Yes, I do.

03:22.536 --> 03:24.204
‐ Look, if you ask me,
I feel like we're taking

03:24.204 --> 03:26.290
this whole self‐improvement thing
a little too far.

03:26.290 --> 03:28.083
‐ I didn't ask, but what's
that supposed to mean?

03:28.083 --> 03:30.252
‐ It means that‐‐ Whoa, God!

03:31.003 --> 03:34.089
Look, if we keep getting better,
eventually we'll be perfect,

03:34.089 --> 03:35.632
right? Then what?

03:36.633 --> 03:38.218
‐ Maybe you'll be
a perfect little asshole.

03:38.218 --> 03:39.469
‐ I'm not being an asshole.

03:39.469 --> 03:41.054
I just don't understand
why I'm going to this place.

03:41.054 --> 03:43.599
‐ We're going 'cause we have issues,
Benjamin...

03:45.434 --> 03:46.852
with us.

03:46.852 --> 03:48.645
That should mean more to you
than your fucking car.

03:49.897 --> 03:51.190
We need something dramatic.

03:52.149 --> 03:54.109
BEN: Yeah, this is definitely dramatic.

03:54.109 --> 03:56.236
Yo, if I fuck up my suspension‐‐
[Ben grunting]

03:56.236 --> 03:58.238
♪ It's a Good Day playing ♪

03:58.238 --> 04:02.075
‐ ♪ Yes, it's a good day
for singin' a song ♪

04:02.075 --> 04:06.038
♪ And it's a good day for movin' along ♪

04:06.038 --> 04:10.209
♪ Yes, it's a good day
How could anything be wrong ♪

04:10.209 --> 04:11.502
‐ Uh.
‐ ♪ A good day ♪

04:11.502 --> 04:13.462
♪ From mornin' till night ♪

04:15.047 --> 04:19.259
‐ Wellness here I come.
[chuckles] Frances 2.0.

04:19.885 --> 04:21.053
Get ready.

04:22.638 --> 04:24.139
Yeah, get ready.

04:24.139 --> 04:25.599
‐ ♪ ...and nothin' to lose ♪

04:25.599 --> 04:28.268
♪ A good day
From mornin' till night ♪

04:28.268 --> 04:31.438
‐ Little shit. Not even a phone call, huh?

04:32.147 --> 04:34.149
Why not? Would it be too courteous?

04:35.526 --> 04:37.361
[cell phone ringing]
Ah‐ha. Oh.

04:39.154 --> 04:40.197
[sighs]

04:40.864 --> 04:42.074
Hello?

04:42.074 --> 04:44.785
ERIN [on phone]:
Hey. So have we achieved nirvana yet?

04:44.785 --> 04:48.413
‐ [laughs] Still a ways off
from infinite serenity.

04:48.413 --> 04:50.541
ERIN: Okay. Well, you need to give
this a real chance, honey.

04:50.541 --> 04:51.959
‐ I am giving this a real cha‐‐

04:51.959 --> 04:54.211
I'm literally going there right now.

04:54.211 --> 04:55.712
That's giving it a chance.

04:55.712 --> 04:57.881
ERIN: And do not even think about him.

04:57.881 --> 04:59.132
He's an asshole.

04:59.132 --> 05:00.968
‐ I wasn't. If I could just get my friends

05:00.968 --> 05:02.886
to stop calling and bringing him up.

05:02.886 --> 05:05.430
Any ideas how I could do that?
ERIN: Oh.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.599
Have you heard from your agent?

05:07.599 --> 05:09.810
‐ I have not, but now
you've brought up him

05:09.810 --> 05:12.145
and work, so you got anything else

05:12.145 --> 05:15.566
you wanna throw at me?
ERIN: Just that I love you.

05:15.566 --> 05:18.277
The new book is fantastic.
You are fantastic,

05:18.277 --> 05:21.697
and you're going to have a fabulous
10 days at Tranquillum.

05:21.697 --> 05:24.658
‐ Yes. I know. I feel the same way.

05:24.658 --> 05:27.202
Come back a whole new me.

05:27.202 --> 05:29.872
I'm sure everyone will like
that one better. [laughs]

05:30.247 --> 05:32.916
ERIN: Well, I like this one.

05:33.876 --> 05:36.211
‐ Thanks. Oh, Erin, it's my agent,

05:36.211 --> 05:37.921
I'm gonna have to call you back.
Love you.

05:37.921 --> 05:39.423
ERIN: Call me back!
I love you!

05:39.923 --> 05:41.884
‐ Hey there.
MARTY [on phone]: Frances?

05:41.884 --> 05:44.386
‐ So, how's the book biz going today?

05:44.386 --> 05:45.512
[laughs]
MARTY: Whoa! You just‐‐

05:45.512 --> 05:46.805
you just sound so upbeat!

05:46.805 --> 05:49.183
‐ I'm on my way to that health retreat
I told you about.

05:49.183 --> 05:52.269
I'm just trying to put myself
in a positive state of mind.

05:52.269 --> 05:54.229
MARTY: Yeah, well, remember
those people who died

05:54.229 --> 05:55.355
in that sweat lodge?

05:55.355 --> 05:56.982
They thought they were being enlightened

05:56.982 --> 05:58.817
when in reality they were being cooked.

05:58.817 --> 06:01.195
‐ This is nothing like that.
This place looks amazing.

06:01.195 --> 06:03.322
I'm just going there for some healing.

06:03.322 --> 06:05.991
You know, massage.
Maybe some gentle fasting.

06:06.742 --> 06:08.160
MARTY: Great, well,

06:08.160 --> 06:10.162
I'm not the bearer of good news, Franny.

06:10.954 --> 06:12.080
‐ What is that supposed to mean?

06:13.165 --> 06:15.751
MARTY: I think it is beautifully written,

06:15.751 --> 06:18.754
I really, really do.
[clearing throat]

06:21.048 --> 06:23.175
‐ W‐‐ wait a minute. Are‐‐ are you s‐‐

06:23.175 --> 06:26.345
are you saying they don't‐‐
they don't want the book?

06:27.471 --> 06:29.223
MARTY: There's no easy way
to say this, Franny,

06:29.223 --> 06:30.849
so I'm just gonna tell you.

06:31.517 --> 06:33.393
They want to buy you
out of your contract.

06:35.854 --> 06:37.773
I'm so sorry about this, Franny,

06:37.773 --> 06:39.399
especially after everything that happened

06:39.399 --> 06:41.109
with that horrendous grifter man.

06:41.109 --> 06:42.736
I mean, I just feel so awful for you.

06:42.736 --> 06:45.405
‐ I do not wanna talk about this with you.

06:45.822 --> 06:47.824
[Frances breathing heavily]

06:48.951 --> 06:50.327
[scoffs, pants]

06:51.245 --> 06:52.287
That's it.

06:53.080 --> 06:56.250
I'm done. This is how it ends.

06:56.250 --> 06:57.835
Dead to the fucking world!

06:59.044 --> 07:00.254
Fucking dead!

07:01.296 --> 07:04.842
[grunting] You're dead
to the fucking world!

07:05.217 --> 07:07.970
[screaming, crying]
Oh, my God.

07:07.970 --> 07:09.263
TONY: Hello?

07:09.263 --> 07:11.306
[gasps, breathes heavily]

07:11.306 --> 07:12.766
You okay?
[Frances stammers]

07:13.934 --> 07:16.061
You‐‐ do you need some help, Miss?

07:16.061 --> 07:18.313
‐ No. I'm‐‐ I'm‐‐ I'm good. I'm good.

07:18.313 --> 07:19.731
‐ You don't seem good.

07:19.731 --> 07:23.944
‐ Well, I was just having
a quiet moment of despair.

07:23.944 --> 07:27.030
‐ Okay. Well, that's your idea
of a quiet moment?

07:27.030 --> 07:28.365
'Cause you seemed...

07:28.365 --> 07:29.449
You're screaming like a banshee.

07:29.449 --> 07:30.742
That's why I pulled over.

07:31.660 --> 07:33.328
‐ Well, I'm sorry. I apologize.
‐ It's okay.

07:33.328 --> 07:36.790
‐ I thought I was in the middle
of nowhere, completely alone.

07:36.790 --> 07:38.834
Clearly, that is not the case.
‐ Are you sick?

07:40.752 --> 07:42.546
‐ I beg your pardon?
‐ You seem to be having

07:42.546 --> 07:45.924
some kind of a mental breakdown
episode sort of thing.

07:45.924 --> 07:48.135
I'm not judging, you know, I got, uh‐‐

07:48.135 --> 07:49.970
I got mental illness in my own family.

07:50.470 --> 07:52.055
‐ Is that right? I'm fine, thank you.

07:52.055 --> 07:54.099
‐ You know, it's not normal
to be screaming...

07:55.100 --> 07:56.435
"dead to the fuckin' world"

07:56.435 --> 07:58.103
at the top of your lungs, you know?

07:58.103 --> 07:59.188
‐ You know what it is?

08:00.063 --> 08:01.064
I was having a hot flash.

08:02.482 --> 08:03.442
‐ Oh.

08:03.984 --> 08:06.320
‐ So I'm good. Thank you so much.

08:06.320 --> 08:08.238
‐ Do you take supplements?
[Frances grunts]

08:08.238 --> 08:11.575
‐ [exhales] I'm sorry. W‐‐ [scoffs]

08:11.575 --> 08:13.785
‐ Proges‐‐ Progesterone? Progesterone.

08:13.785 --> 08:17.331
I heard that helps.
‐ Are we actually
having this conversation right now?

08:17.331 --> 08:19.333
‐ What's with the tone, lady?
‐ I don't have a tone.

08:19.333 --> 08:23.045
I am just not used
to complete strangers prescribing

08:23.045 --> 08:25.422
hormone replacement therapy...

08:25.422 --> 08:27.466
curbside!
‐ Apologies.

08:28.050 --> 08:30.010
I can see now that you're a tragic person.

08:30.010 --> 08:31.011
Have a good day.

08:33.555 --> 08:35.098
[door shuts, car starting]

08:39.228 --> 08:40.771
[engine revs]

08:42.606 --> 08:43.982
♪ upbeat music playing ♪

08:47.277 --> 08:48.820
SAM: Good morning.
‐ Hey.

08:49.071 --> 08:50.364
SAM: Okay.

08:55.244 --> 08:56.870
Headed to Tranquillum, I see.

08:58.372 --> 08:59.540
‐ Why would you say that?

08:59.540 --> 09:02.000
‐ You're loading up
on all the forbidden food items.

09:02.000 --> 09:04.127
‐ Oh, I'm going there, too.

09:05.379 --> 09:06.839
‐ Excellent.

09:06.839 --> 09:08.674
SAM: You'd be lucky
if you get past the front door

09:08.674 --> 09:10.092
with this stuff.
[cell phone chiming]

09:13.554 --> 09:15.013
They'll be taking that, too.

09:15.848 --> 09:17.015
They don't allow...

09:17.015 --> 09:19.017
‐ Excuse me?
‐ ... phones at Tranquillum.

09:19.560 --> 09:21.061
LARS: What have you heard about the place?

09:21.061 --> 09:23.438
‐ Mm, not much. Uh, the guests
go in looking one way.

09:23.438 --> 09:24.606
Come out looking another.

09:24.606 --> 09:26.358
So she must be doing something to them.

09:26.358 --> 09:29.111
‐ And, uh, have you met her?
The woman that runs it?

09:29.611 --> 09:31.238
‐ No, no, but...

09:32.614 --> 09:34.116
from what I've heard, I'd like to.

09:34.116 --> 09:36.660
‐ Supposedly she completely
changes people.

09:36.660 --> 09:40.998
I mean, that's why I'm going.
To be transformed. [laughs]

09:42.791 --> 09:43.959
‐ Good luck with that.

09:47.129 --> 09:48.380
[door bells jingle]

09:50.132 --> 09:51.300
[Carmel sighs]
SAM: Hi.

09:51.300 --> 09:53.177
‐ Hi.
♪ mid‐tempo music playing ♪

10:10.068 --> 10:11.486
MARTY [on phone]:
It's the market, you know.

10:11.486 --> 10:14.323
Romance has taken the worst hit.
It won't be forever.

10:14.323 --> 10:16.408
FRANCES: This tension
is not good for my back, Marty.

10:16.408 --> 10:17.784
MARTY: Franny, come on, stop it.

10:17.784 --> 10:20.579
Don't‐‐ don't waste your energy
on this nonsense.

10:20.579 --> 10:22.331
Just try to forget about it.
Have a great time.

10:22.331 --> 10:24.458
FRANCES: I'm a blight
on feminism because I described

10:24.458 --> 10:27.544
the eye color of‐‐ of my‐‐ my hero?

10:28.337 --> 10:29.421
Oh.

10:31.882 --> 10:34.134
‐ Namaste. Welcome to Tranquillum.

10:34.134 --> 10:36.887
‐ Ooh, um, so excited to hear about it.

10:36.887 --> 10:39.014
Give me one second. Just one second.

10:39.014 --> 10:40.933
They said I should have killed off Jane.

10:40.933 --> 10:42.476
Who kills their main character? Who?

10:42.476 --> 10:44.645
[indistinct chatter]
‐ You must be Frances? Come.

10:44.645 --> 10:47.356
One journey ends and another begins.

10:47.356 --> 10:48.941
[engine revving]

10:48.941 --> 10:51.777
FRANCES: Oh, how can they say
I hate women?

10:51.777 --> 10:54.530
[scoffing] I can't hate women.
I am a woman.

10:54.530 --> 10:56.031
And I'm crazy about myself.

10:56.031 --> 10:58.158
[indistinct chatter]

10:58.158 --> 11:00.285
BEN: Look. It's not too late
to call this whole thing off.

11:00.285 --> 11:01.286
JESSICA: Ben, please, we're here.

11:01.828 --> 11:03.830
‐ I just feel like this is something
we can work on ourselves.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.499
‐ We've been working on it.

11:05.916 --> 11:08.794
We're not in a good place obviously,

11:08.794 --> 11:11.338
and either we try or...

11:12.256 --> 11:13.674
[motor running]

11:13.674 --> 11:15.425
[grunts] ...we don't.
[horn honking]

11:15.926 --> 11:17.678
[horn continues honking]

11:19.012 --> 11:20.973
‐ What the fuck is your problem, man?

11:23.016 --> 11:23.976
‐ No problem.

11:24.601 --> 11:26.770
I just need you to nudge it up
a little so I can pull in.

11:26.770 --> 11:28.438
‐ So you're gonna just keep
blowing your horn like that?

11:28.897 --> 11:30.983
‐ Like what? It's a horn,

11:30.983 --> 11:32.109
it's not a musical instrument.

11:32.109 --> 11:34.152
You just, you know, push.

11:34.152 --> 11:35.863
[horn honking]

11:35.863 --> 11:37.406
See? It's only got the one note.

11:37.406 --> 11:39.575
LULU: Namaste! Welcome to Tranquillum.

11:40.951 --> 11:42.536
‐ Oh, my God, your skin is amazing.

11:42.536 --> 11:44.746
Ben, look at her skin!
LULU: I'm Lulu,

11:44.746 --> 11:46.039
one of the Wellness Consultants here.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.291
‐ Cool skin.
‐ Hi.

11:47.291 --> 11:48.542
LULU: You guys ready for the tour?

11:48.542 --> 11:49.918
‐ Yes.
‐ Guess so.

11:49.918 --> 11:51.253
LULU: Great!

11:51.253 --> 11:53.046
Uh, we'll have to unburden you
from that soon.

11:53.046 --> 11:54.339
BEN: Oh, shit.
JESSICA: What?

11:54.339 --> 11:55.674
LULU: It hurts, but it's so worth it.

11:55.674 --> 11:59.386
‐ But I'm‐‐ Do you mean like‐‐
like the whole time?

12:00.429 --> 12:02.347
But it's my phone.
[horn honking]

12:02.347 --> 12:04.266
TONY: Hello?
‐ Can we‐‐ can we

12:04.266 --> 12:06.018
eject him, evict him, get him out of here?

12:06.018 --> 12:07.477
FRANCES: You know‐‐ You know what that is?

12:07.477 --> 12:08.562
I know exactly what‐‐

12:08.562 --> 12:10.564
That's‐‐ because it's just so in vogue now

12:10.564 --> 12:12.983
to kill your characters.
Well, they're my babies.

12:12.983 --> 12:14.568
Okay, I'm sorry if I'm not a baby‐killer.

12:14.568 --> 12:16.236
I don't even wound my characters.

12:16.737 --> 12:18.363
[indistinct chatter]

12:20.240 --> 12:22.743
DELILAH: After we get
you checked in, I would suggest

12:22.743 --> 12:26.413
a little forest bathing
to lower your cortisol.

12:26.413 --> 12:28.790
‐ Oh, wow. That sounds nice.

12:28.790 --> 12:30.083
[both laugh]

12:30.083 --> 12:31.710
‐ We have an award‐winning arboretum.

12:31.710 --> 12:33.086
FRANCES: And I'll tell you, what‐‐

12:33.086 --> 12:34.713
what I've never been called is dangerous.

12:34.713 --> 12:35.881
How would I even be dangerous?

12:35.881 --> 12:36.882
Wait‐‐ With‐‐ I'm‐‐

12:36.882 --> 12:37.841
CARMEL: Oh, no.
‐ I'm sorry.

12:37.841 --> 12:39.134
‐ No, I'm sorry. I'm sorry. No worries.

12:39.134 --> 12:40.969
‐ [Frances sighing] I'm sorry.
‐ Uh, I'm Carmel.

12:40.969 --> 12:42.804
‐ Yeah. It's, uh...
‐ No, get it. I get it.

12:42.804 --> 12:45.015
I was just on the phone with my kids, too.

12:45.015 --> 12:46.975
I miss them so much.
‐ Oh, yeah. Oh, no.

12:46.975 --> 12:48.727
‐ This is Bella. This is‐‐
‐ That's not‐‐ No, that's not‐‐

12:48.727 --> 12:52.105
I'm not doing‐‐ I'm‐‐ I'm‐‐
It's a work call.

12:52.105 --> 12:54.274
CARMEL: Oh.
‐ I‐‐ I do something
for a living.

12:54.274 --> 12:54.983
So I don't do ki‐‐
CARMEL: Oh, well I...

12:54.983 --> 12:56.235
‐ I‐‐ Not meaning‐‐ I don't mean...

12:56.235 --> 12:57.486
CARMEL: Yeah.
‐ ...to diminish.

12:57.486 --> 12:58.862
I just‐‐ I have to...
‐ No. No, no.

12:58.862 --> 12:59.821
‐ ...take this.
‐ I‐‐ Yeah.

12:59.821 --> 13:01.907
‐ I appreciate what you do. I was‐‐ God.

13:01.907 --> 13:03.492
‐ I get‐‐ No, I‐‐ I understand.

13:03.492 --> 13:06.036
‐ Carmel. It'll be fine, I promise.

13:06.620 --> 13:07.621
They aren't in there.

13:08.997 --> 13:09.998
They're in here.

13:11.124 --> 13:12.084
And in here.

13:13.710 --> 13:14.837
[exhales heavily]

13:18.382 --> 13:19.758
♪

13:21.885 --> 13:23.387
‐ You're so pretty.

13:23.387 --> 13:26.682
May I ask, is everybody
here beautiful? [laughs]

13:26.682 --> 13:28.559
‐ As a matter of fact, yes.

13:28.559 --> 13:31.603
‐ Oh, wow.
‐ Including you, Carmel.

13:36.650 --> 13:38.110
‐ Thank you.
‐ Yeah.

13:38.652 --> 13:40.153
‐ It's okay. All right?
‐ No.

13:40.153 --> 13:41.572
I‐‐ I just need to pull something.

13:41.572 --> 13:43.156
‐ Okay. No‐‐
‐ I need to pull something up.

13:43.156 --> 13:44.783
‐ Frances. Frances. Frances.
‐ And then‐‐ I just need to‐‐

13:44.783 --> 13:45.659
‐ Frances.
‐ Mm‐hmm.

13:45.659 --> 13:48.203
‐ Imagine you didn't, because you don't.

13:49.246 --> 13:51.915
You actually don't... need to.

13:54.877 --> 13:56.879
‐ Okay. Here's the thing,
something's come up.

13:57.421 --> 14:00.007
So I'm gonna have to leave.
‐ Something always does.

14:00.757 --> 14:02.009
But you're here.

14:03.218 --> 14:05.304
Be here, Frances.

14:07.181 --> 14:08.473
[sighs]

14:11.643 --> 14:13.896
‐ You're very good at this.
DELILAH: Sign here, please.

14:14.688 --> 14:18.609
‐ Hi. S‐‐ um, sorry about before.
