I mean, you rarely see engineering

15:52.286 --> 15:53.704
like this in a resort.

15:53.704 --> 15:56.707
The‐‐ the‐‐ the craftsmanship,
the attention to detail.

15:56.707 --> 15:57.749
Incredible.

15:59.168 --> 16:01.295
Hey! Napoleon.

16:02.379 --> 16:04.089
‐ Genghis Khan... Patton?

16:04.089 --> 16:06.383
‐ Oh, I get it. No, uh, Napoleon Marconi,

16:06.383 --> 16:08.218
that's my name.
FRANCES: Oh, Frances.

16:08.218 --> 16:09.928
I thought we were doing a military thing.

16:09.928 --> 16:11.555
I think I lost my guide.

16:11.555 --> 16:13.807
‐ Yeah, it's super to meet you.
You here for the, uh,

16:13.807 --> 16:16.226
10‐day retreat? Us 2.0?

16:16.226 --> 16:19.688
‐ I certainly am.
YAO: Ah, there you are.

16:19.688 --> 16:21.273
Thought we had a runner for a second.

16:21.273 --> 16:23.025
‐ Oh. What is this?

16:23.025 --> 16:25.277
‐ Ah, tailored specifically
to your metabolic needs,

16:25.277 --> 16:26.778
so please do not share.

16:26.778 --> 16:28.739
Also it has been precisely constructed,

16:28.739 --> 16:30.157
so please be sure to drink it all.

16:30.157 --> 16:31.200
FRANCES: That is just the best.

16:31.200 --> 16:33.202
‐ Meet my beautiful, beautiful girls.

16:33.202 --> 16:35.454
Wife Heather. Daughter Zoe.

16:35.454 --> 16:37.206
‐ Hi.
‐ Pleasure to meet you.

16:37.206 --> 16:39.374
‐ Likewise. So what brings you here?

16:39.374 --> 16:41.543
Because I have to say,
you look pretty perfect.

16:41.543 --> 16:42.836
‐ Why would you say something like that?

16:44.129 --> 16:48.383
‐ I meant it as a compliment.
I... S‐‐ sorry if‐‐

16:48.383 --> 16:51.678
‐ Uh, I think we're gonna explore
the hot springs, maybe get a quick soak,

16:51.678 --> 16:55.015
do a few laps in the pool,
maybe even visit the sacred spa.

16:55.015 --> 16:56.475
DELILAH: Should I show you
the hot springs?

16:56.475 --> 16:58.977
‐ Please do. Ciao, Frances.
‐ Ciao.

16:58.977 --> 17:01.188
NAPOLEON: C'mon, ladies.
Jump start on bliss.

17:02.189 --> 17:03.357
‐ Nice to meet you.

17:07.778 --> 17:08.737
Heather's a bitch.

17:09.863 --> 17:12.157
‐ Okay. Uh, your room is this way.

17:14.159 --> 17:15.410
♪ ominous music playing ♪

17:18.121 --> 17:20.207
LARS:
Wow. You have an MRI machine?

17:20.207 --> 17:22.709
‐ Oh yeah, we've got all
the toys here at Tranquillum.

17:24.044 --> 17:25.671
‐ How much does an MRI machine cost?

17:25.671 --> 17:27.673
GLORY: I wouldn't know, I'm afraid.

17:27.673 --> 17:29.132
‐ I hear tell that Bill Gates

17:29.132 --> 17:31.051
funded all of this,
or at least put up a lot

17:31.051 --> 17:33.971
of the initial seed money. Is it true?

17:33.971 --> 17:35.472
‐ I wouldn't know.

17:35.472 --> 17:37.432
‐ Awful lot of not knowing going on.

17:38.392 --> 17:39.434
What's this?

17:39.434 --> 17:41.061
GLORY: It's just our legal disclaimer.

17:41.061 --> 17:43.689
LARS: Does anyone come all
the way here and not sign it?

17:43.689 --> 17:45.649
‐ You would be the first not to sign.

17:47.359 --> 17:48.318
LARS: Hmm.

17:50.946 --> 17:55.826
"Clients are prohibited
from posting about Tranquillum

17:55.826 --> 17:57.953
on social media platforms."
DELILAH: Hmm.

17:57.953 --> 17:59.580
‐ Hmm. So,

17:59.580 --> 18:02.457
how do you attract new guests?
‐ Word of mouth.

18:05.002 --> 18:07.671
‐ That's an impressive smile.
DELILAH: I like to think so.

18:07.671 --> 18:09.006
[Lars scoffing]

18:14.303 --> 18:15.053
‐ What's that?

18:15.888 --> 18:17.931
‐ Oh. Blood draw. Standard practice.

18:17.931 --> 18:19.975
‐ That's standard? I've already submitted

18:19.975 --> 18:22.019
my medical records, um,

18:22.019 --> 18:23.812
which I found to be a tad bit bizarre‐‐

18:23.812 --> 18:25.898
‐ We do a blood intake every few days.

18:25.898 --> 18:28.317
It was outlined
in the document you just signed.

18:28.317 --> 18:31.111
It's part of how we tailor
your wellness journey.

18:32.988 --> 18:34.323
‐ All right. Fine.

18:36.033 --> 18:36.950
Which arm?

18:38.076 --> 18:39.119
[chuckles]

18:39.912 --> 18:40.996
‐ This won't hurt a bit.

18:42.331 --> 18:43.624
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

18:47.127 --> 18:51.548
CARMEL: You are brave. You are powerful.

18:51.840 --> 18:53.592
You shall be new again.

18:56.053 --> 19:01.350
[exhales] You shall be
who you came here to be.

19:03.644 --> 19:04.645
Yes.

19:06.730 --> 19:08.732
[exhales] Get a grip, Carmel.

19:11.944 --> 19:13.070
[trickling]

19:27.417 --> 19:30.337
‐ Oh. Come on. [gasps]
‐ Oh, oh, oh!

19:30.337 --> 19:32.089
‐ I'm‐‐ I'm sorry,
‐ [Tony grunting] Sorry!

19:32.089 --> 19:36.134
‐ No, I'm so sorry.
I was‐‐ I was forest bathing

19:36.134 --> 19:38.345
and‐‐ and I mistook you for a creek.

19:38.345 --> 19:40.055
TONY: My bad. I shouldn't have done that.

19:40.055 --> 19:42.057
I just‐‐ You know, I‐‐ I had
to go and, uh...

19:42.057 --> 19:43.475
‐ Yeah.
[Tony stammering]

19:43.475 --> 19:45.185
‐ ...my‐‐ my wellness consultant
was nowhere to be found.

19:45.185 --> 19:46.228
CARMEL: Hmm.

19:46.228 --> 19:48.438
TONY: Just don't rat me out
to the warden, okay?

19:48.438 --> 19:51.692
‐ No. The‐‐ Wait, the warden?
‐ Uh, you know.

19:51.692 --> 19:54.069
The Russian lady.
‐ Oh, have you met her?

19:54.862 --> 19:56.405
‐ Uh, no. Not yet. You?

19:56.405 --> 19:59.116
‐ No, I haven't. But I can't wait.

19:59.116 --> 20:00.993
I mean, I've heard so much about her.

20:00.993 --> 20:02.035
[chuckles]

20:03.412 --> 20:04.705
‐ Sorry, I just be...

20:06.164 --> 20:07.916
God, you look so familiar.

20:07.916 --> 20:09.293
I don't‐‐ I‐‐
‐ No. I'm not.

20:12.754 --> 20:15.465
‐ Yeah. I'm Carmel.

20:17.009 --> 20:19.303
‐ Tony. What are you in for?

20:20.095 --> 20:23.015
‐ Weight loss. Esteem building,

20:23.015 --> 20:25.058
mind and body transformation.
And what about you?

20:26.602 --> 20:27.769
‐ Yeah, no, same thing.

20:28.604 --> 20:30.355
‐ Are you married?
‐ Am I married?

20:30.898 --> 20:33.483
Uh, fuck, this isn't one
of those places, is it?

20:33.483 --> 20:35.027
‐ Wait, what? What do you‐‐
‐ Uh...

20:35.027 --> 20:36.195
‐ What do you mean by that?

20:36.195 --> 20:38.780
‐ Lifelong bachelor.
Rest of my life, anyway.

20:38.780 --> 20:41.200
So, I gotta go finish here, okay?

20:41.200 --> 20:44.203
I‐‐ I didn't even get to the shake.
Nice to meet you, Chanelle.

20:44.203 --> 20:45.704
[urine trickling]

20:45.704 --> 20:47.080
[Tony grunting]
‐ Yeah. [clears throat]

20:48.957 --> 20:50.250
YAO: Right this way.

20:50.250 --> 20:52.294
♪ tranquil music playing ♪

20:52.294 --> 20:53.420
‐ Oh...

20:55.589 --> 20:56.465
wow.

20:57.716 --> 20:58.717
This, um...

20:59.635 --> 21:01.136
this is Heaven.

21:04.139 --> 21:06.391
YAO: Welcome to Tranquillum.
[Frances sighing]

21:06.391 --> 21:08.393
Your wellness journey
has begun, Frances.

21:08.977 --> 21:12.564
‐ You know, I have been feeling
rather unwell lately.

21:13.774 --> 21:16.777
‐ Hmm. Yes, I know you have.

21:19.947 --> 21:21.365
‐ This is going to be the best thing.

21:22.115 --> 21:23.325
I just know it.

21:25.827 --> 21:27.412
It has to be.

21:30.332 --> 21:31.750
YAO: We'll get you well, Frances.

21:33.502 --> 21:36.505
We'll get you feeling
as well as you've ever felt

21:37.130 --> 21:38.507
in your whole life.

21:39.258 --> 21:40.259
‐ Yeah.

21:49.977 --> 21:50.936
[sobs]

21:52.479 --> 21:53.355
[cries]

22:09.079 --> 22:11.123
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

22:13.417 --> 22:16.420
[sobs]

22:24.469 --> 22:26.263
[gasps] God... [sniffles]

22:28.307 --> 22:29.600
How did you get in here?

22:30.767 --> 22:32.686
MASHA: I came in through the door.

22:35.939 --> 22:37.357
I'm Masha.

22:37.357 --> 22:40.694
♪ ethereal music playing ♪

22:43.113 --> 22:44.323
‐ You're her.

22:46.825 --> 22:48.368
‐ Why are you crying, Frances?

22:48.994 --> 22:51.580
‐ Oh, you know. [chuckles]
Just a little bit of...

22:51.580 --> 22:54.791
[sniffles] ..."my career
is over" kind of thing,

22:54.791 --> 22:59.087
bit of menopause, you know,
mix in a little bad relationship

22:59.087 --> 23:01.924
and a dash of crippling shame.

23:01.924 --> 23:03.383
‐ We're gonna get you well.

23:04.218 --> 23:05.594
♪ mid‐tempo music playing ♪

23:08.597 --> 23:10.974
‐ You know, uh, I almost didn't come.

23:10.974 --> 23:12.226
[chuckles, sniffles]

23:13.143 --> 23:15.896
And then, when I did get here...

23:17.397 --> 23:18.899
I really thought about leaving.

23:20.609 --> 23:22.986
MASHA: Nearly everyone here
almost didn't come.

23:23.487 --> 23:25.405
They sense it's going to take courage.

23:26.657 --> 23:27.658
And it'll be...

23:29.034 --> 23:30.786
sometimes unpleasant.

23:30.786 --> 23:32.496
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

23:32.496 --> 23:33.997
And I'll tell you something else.

23:33.997 --> 23:35.415
The people who come here, most of them,

23:35.415 --> 23:37.584
they have fairly good lives.
Comfortable, even.

23:38.877 --> 23:40.420
They come for the suffering.

23:45.342 --> 23:46.510
‐ I don't want to suffer.

23:47.636 --> 23:49.221
‐ You're already suffering.

23:57.938 --> 23:58.897
[exhales heavily]

24:02.234 --> 24:03.360
[whistles]

24:06.738 --> 24:10.117
‐ No. What the hell? Yup, all right.

24:11.785 --> 24:12.744
What?

24:14.997 --> 24:15.914
‐ Nothing.

24:17.165 --> 24:18.667
‐ Why is Zoe in another room?

24:20.794 --> 24:23.630
‐ Because the rooms
are double occupancy, darling.

24:23.630 --> 24:25.507
She loves having her own room,
you kidding?

24:25.507 --> 24:26.508
‐ Did she tell you that?

24:26.884 --> 24:28.719
‐ Well, what 20‐year‐old
doesn't want to get away

24:28.719 --> 24:30.387
from her parents?
‐ Perhaps, our...

24:31.513 --> 24:33.015
20‐year‐old.

24:33.015 --> 24:36.810
Perhaps, on this weekend...
of all weekends.

24:38.562 --> 24:39.813
[breathes heavily]

24:44.359 --> 24:45.402
[gasps]

24:50.741 --> 24:53.660
NAPOLEON: Just ride it out, sweetheart.
Yeah. Hmm.

24:54.661 --> 24:55.704
[breathes heavily]

24:59.625 --> 25:00.626
Hey.

25:05.631 --> 25:07.424
I thought I might hit the hot springs

25:07.424 --> 25:09.718
before orientation. Join me?

25:10.844 --> 25:13.639
‐ You go, honey.
I think I'll go for a run.

25:19.853 --> 25:21.730
LARS: No, I haven't met her yet.

25:21.730 --> 25:23.690
The official orientation is this evening.

25:25.192 --> 25:26.401
But it's fucked up...

25:27.736 --> 25:29.154
that I can already tell.

25:30.447 --> 25:32.366
Mm‐hmm. I'll ring you again tomorrow.

25:35.369 --> 25:36.745
[phone trilling]

25:37.663 --> 25:38.705
RAY [on phone]: Hello?
‐ Hey.

25:40.123 --> 25:41.333
RAY: Lars?

25:42.292 --> 25:43.961
‐ Forget my voice already?
RAY: Where are you?

25:44.795 --> 25:47.005
LARS: I'm at some fucked‐up spa thing.

25:48.382 --> 25:49.258
RAY: Again?

25:50.133 --> 25:52.177
Cool. [clearing throat]

25:52.177 --> 25:54.555
LARS: It's for work.
‐ Yeah, okay.

25:54.555 --> 25:57.182
LARS: I'm just gonna
be off‐grid for 10 days,

25:57.182 --> 25:59.017
I wanted you to know. Just in case...

26:01.103 --> 26:02.980
I don't know...
‐ Lars, where you go,

26:02.980 --> 26:04.481
that's no longer

26:04.481 --> 26:06.233
any of my business. Is it?

26:07.109 --> 26:08.360
‐ All right.

26:10.737 --> 26:12.656
Well, uh‐‐
‐ Oh, enjoy your 10 days.

26:12.656 --> 26:13.824
‐ Ray.
[line drops]

26:19.830 --> 26:21.540
[birds chirping]

26:21.540 --> 26:22.958
[twig snaps]

26:28.714 --> 26:30.048
So many rules here,

26:31.175 --> 26:34.011
I would've thought eavesdropping
must be on the list.

26:34.011 --> 26:35.679
‐ Wait, how do you still have a phone?

26:37.306 --> 26:39.016
‐ I don't have a phone.
‐ Right, right.

26:39.016 --> 26:40.017
You just have a‐‐

26:40.475 --> 26:42.519
you just have a watch
and an earpiece and...

26:45.522 --> 26:47.149
‐ Lars Lee.

26:47.149 --> 26:48.233
‐ Zoe Marconi.

26:49.109 --> 26:51.778
‐ And what brings
a Zoe Marconi to Tranquillum?

26:52.654 --> 26:55.616
‐ Um... my pare‐‐ My parents.

26:56.867 --> 26:57.993
‐ Hmm.

26:58.869 --> 27:01.538
‐ Yeah, what brings a Lars Lee? [sniffs]

27:01.538 --> 27:03.457
And why do you think
this place is fucked up?

27:05.626 --> 27:07.419
‐ Well, they all are, aren't they?

27:08.462 --> 27:09.505
"Wellness retreats,"

27:09.505 --> 27:11.673
just another construct
to separate rich people

27:11.673 --> 27:12.674
from their money.

27:12.674 --> 27:15.302
Get them to feel good
about themselves in the process.

27:16.178 --> 27:17.721
It's such utter crap.

27:17.721 --> 27:19.848
‐ And yet here you are,
spending your money.

27:19.848 --> 27:21.433
Feeling good about yourself.

27:21.433 --> 27:24.686
‐ Wow. You and I could actually
be friends.

27:24.686 --> 27:25.854
[chuckles]

27:25.854 --> 27:29.441
‐ And how would, uh, Ray feel about that?

27:29.816 --> 27:32.152
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

27:32.152 --> 27:35.322
TONY:
Hey, honey, hi. Uh, it's me again.

27:35.322 --> 27:37.574
Just leaving you another message. Um...

27:37.574 --> 27:40.118
Look, I'm going to be off
the grid for a few days.

27:40.118 --> 27:41.703
I'm at a wellness retreat.

27:43.205 --> 27:45.874
[chuckles] Anyway,
I'm gonna be unreachable.

27:45.874 --> 27:47.000
Not that you care.

27:48.961 --> 27:50.337
Sorry, uh...

27:53.715 --> 27:57.219
I love you. It's, you know, I'll, uh...

28:00.389 --> 28:01.723
Yeah, love you. Okay.

28:03.559 --> 28:04.935
[gasps]

28:04.935 --> 28:06.728
‐ Tony. I'll need to take your phone now.

28:07.187 --> 28:08.981
‐ Yeah, I was just leaving
a message for my daughter.

28:08.981 --> 28:11.441
‐ Got it. But we have rules, so...

28:12.818 --> 28:14.820
the phone, please?
‐ Uh, yeah, look.

28:16.697 --> 28:18.365
I don't think
I'm really supposed to be here.

28:19.491 --> 28:22.578
I mean, the whole thing
was kind of random.

28:22.578 --> 28:24.246
I was having a terrible fucking day,

28:24.246 --> 28:28.250
and I Googled "spa."
And then to save a little time,

28:28.250 --> 28:30.961
I typed in "most expensive"
and your place popped up,

28:30.961 --> 28:32.462
but now that I'm here...

28:32.462 --> 28:34.756
‐ We don't really believe
in "random" here.

28:38.260 --> 28:39.595
The phone, please.

28:45.225 --> 28:46.894
♪

28:49.646 --> 28:51.523
Thank you, Tony.
[Tony growls]

28:51.523 --> 28:54.610
♪

28:59.448 --> 29:00.532
[pants]

29:09.917 --> 29:11.627
JESSICA: This is going
to be really good for us.

29:13.504 --> 29:16.590
[chuckles] I can feel it.

29:16.590 --> 29:18.425
[both chuckle]

29:18.425 --> 29:20.010
What do you think?

29:20.010 --> 29:22.095
‐ Yeah, this definitely
feels real good right now.

29:22.095 --> 29:25.516
‐ [chuckles] I think
these mineral baths are, uh,

29:26.391 --> 29:29.144
"aphrodisia‐cal"?
"Aphrodisiacal," is that a word?

29:29.144 --> 29:31.188
‐ Aphrodis‐‐ I don't know,
I think you just made

29:31.188 --> 29:32.898
that one up.
‐ It should be a word.

29:32.898 --> 29:34.149
‐ It definitely should.

29:35.943 --> 29:37.861
‐ You remember right after?

29:37.861 --> 29:39.821
When we went to celebrate at Two Bunch,

29:39.821 --> 29:42.366
and they had to ask us
to leave 'cause we were fucking

29:42.366 --> 29:44.368
so much in the hot springs?
[both chuckle]

29:44.368 --> 29:46.453
‐ I do, that was crazy.

29:49.623 --> 29:50.874
‐ So crazy...

29:52.125 --> 29:53.168
[clicks tongue]

29:54.378 --> 29:55.712
‐ Oh, dear.

29:56.380 --> 29:57.756
‐ What's up, man?
‐ Hi.

29:57.756 --> 30:00.008
‐ Am I intruding?
I‐‐ I'd be the last person

30:00.008 --> 30:02.970
to interrupt a romantic interlude.

30:02.970 --> 30:04.805
‐ Come on in.
‐ The more the merrier.

30:05.347 --> 30:07.057
NAPOLEON: It's just I've been
in a car all day, you know?

30:08.433 --> 30:09.476
All right.

30:10.143 --> 30:12.187
Whoo‐hoo! Wonderful.

30:17.192 --> 30:20.654
Oh, I'm sorry, uh, Napoleon Marconi.

30:20.654 --> 30:22.781
‐ Hi.
‐ Ben Chandler.

30:22.781 --> 30:24.825
This is my wife, Jessica.
‐ Lovely to meet you both.

30:27.661 --> 30:28.787
[groans]

30:30.789 --> 30:32.207
Oh, wait a minute.
You're not the fella

30:32.207 --> 30:34.334
that‐‐ that drives
the Lamborghini, are you?

30:35.252 --> 30:37.588
‐ I am.
‐ Ho, holy moly!

30:38.338 --> 30:40.883
Oh, boy! I'd like
a ride in one of those things.

30:41.800 --> 30:43.260
Before this is all said and done.

30:44.219 --> 30:45.971
BEN: Okay.
‐ Yeah. You see,

30:45.971 --> 30:50.642
I'm just a high school teacher.
We got in here on a discount.

30:50.642 --> 30:53.103
‐ You know what?
I'd be happy to give you a ride.

30:53.103 --> 30:54.396
Maybe even let you take it for a spin.

30:54.396 --> 30:57.900
‐ Oh, my God! You‐‐ you're not kidding?

30:57.900 --> 30:59.109
BEN: Nah.
‐ Wow.

30:59.860 --> 31:01.945
Thank you.
BEN: Yeah, don't mention it.

31:01.945 --> 31:04.031
High school teacher's an admirable job.

31:08.118 --> 31:09.786
