and look at me, and think,

31:47.366 --> 31:48.784
"That guy? Really?"

31:48.784 --> 31:51.203
‐ Oh, I get it. That's funny.
[Napoleon chuckling]

31:51.203 --> 31:52.996
‐ Yeah, you probably don't get
that because, uh,

31:52.996 --> 31:55.457
you're comparably attractive,
you drive a Lamborghini.

31:55.457 --> 31:57.459
‐ Thank you.
NAPOLEON: I'll shut up.

31:57.459 --> 31:59.378
I am perfectly willing to shut up.

31:59.378 --> 32:01.213
I'm a chronically loquacious person

32:01.213 --> 32:02.631
and if you let me talk long enough,

32:02.631 --> 32:06.218
I always seem to find the poop
and step right in it.

32:06.218 --> 32:07.427
[all chuckle]

32:08.554 --> 32:10.055
[blows raspberries]
[Jessica chuckling]

32:10.055 --> 32:12.307
All right, so, I'm going to...

32:13.725 --> 32:16.854
adjourn... to here.

32:19.648 --> 32:21.608
And, uh, wonderful to meet you both.

32:21.608 --> 32:22.901
BOTH: You too.

32:25.070 --> 32:28.448
‐ Whoo! What an extraordinary place.

32:31.410 --> 32:32.953
♪ mid‐tempo music playing ♪

32:35.706 --> 32:36.665
[pants]

32:52.014 --> 32:53.140
[door knocking]

32:54.349 --> 32:57.019
[Delilah sighs]
‐ Are you kidding me?

32:57.019 --> 33:00.564
‐ It's just one.
Tradition, one before every session.

33:02.649 --> 33:06.153
‐ But seriously. We are a health resort.

33:06.153 --> 33:08.614
‐ [sighs] One cigarette
is not going to kill me.

33:10.365 --> 33:12.993
And if it helps me cope,
better for the guests, right?

33:14.578 --> 33:17.539
Something tells me with this group... hmm.

33:18.373 --> 33:20.125
YAO: What? What about this group?

33:21.210 --> 33:24.963
‐ Just... the vibe seems
a little charged, right?

33:26.381 --> 33:28.300
Too many cases in the basket.

33:31.136 --> 33:32.721
‐ Masha knows what she's doing.

33:35.724 --> 33:37.601
♪

33:39.603 --> 33:41.146
[bell tolling]

33:48.028 --> 33:49.696
TONY: What do you mean she curates?

33:50.239 --> 33:53.367
LARS: That's the rumor, she mixes
and matches her guests.

33:53.367 --> 33:55.285
Like a cocktail.
‐ Oh.

33:55.285 --> 33:57.412
Not sure how I made the cut. [grunting]

33:57.412 --> 33:59.164
‐ Well, I guess you must
be really fucked up.

33:59.164 --> 34:01.208
‐ Oh, just your run‐of‐the‐mill asshole.

34:01.834 --> 34:03.210
Oh, hello again.

34:03.627 --> 34:04.628
‐ Hello.

34:05.629 --> 34:07.923
TONY: Feeling any better?
‐ I am, thank you.

34:07.923 --> 34:09.216
TONY: I'm so glad to hear it.

34:09.216 --> 34:11.051
‐ I'm so glad to be able
to share that with you.

34:11.635 --> 34:12.928
Have a wonderful life now.

34:12.928 --> 34:14.555
‐ You too. [chuckles]
‐ Mm‐hmm.

34:16.765 --> 34:19.017
‐ I bring it out of people. It's a gift.

34:19.017 --> 34:20.310
[indistinct chatter]

34:21.228 --> 34:23.564
NAPOLEON: Namaste.
HEATHER: Where are they?

34:23.564 --> 34:24.773
Does anybody know?

34:25.524 --> 34:27.818
Or are we expected to self‐orientate?

34:27.818 --> 34:30.696
‐ Hmm. I think they leave us
alone on purpose.

34:30.696 --> 34:32.072
BEN: Why?

34:32.072 --> 34:33.949
‐ Like in Law & Order,
they always put the suspects

34:33.949 --> 34:36.535
in a room alone at first
to soften them up.

34:36.535 --> 34:39.037
‐ Wait. So, you met her?
FRANCES: I did. Yeah.

34:39.037 --> 34:42.374
‐ And did she give you any idea
what to expect? [sniffs]

34:42.374 --> 34:44.251
‐ Suffering.
‐ Uh‐huh.

34:45.127 --> 34:46.795
I have a very low pain threshold.

34:46.795 --> 34:47.796
NAPOLEON: What else did she say?

34:47.796 --> 34:49.923
‐ Uh, that was really
about the gist of it.

34:49.923 --> 34:52.593
Really, just that, uh,
we'd all come here to suffer.

34:52.593 --> 34:55.637
And I get the feeling she aims to deliver.

34:55.637 --> 34:57.389
Wait till you see her. She's kind

34:57.389 --> 35:00.267
of an amazing mystical
Eastern Bloc unicorn.

35:00.267 --> 35:02.561
[woman gasping]
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

35:02.561 --> 35:05.272
See what I mean?
‐ Namaste.

35:05.272 --> 35:07.733
Welcome to Tranquillum House.

35:13.864 --> 35:16.283
Right now,
you're at the foot of a mountain.

35:16.283 --> 35:19.828
And the summit,
it seems impossibly far away,

35:19.828 --> 35:22.247
and I'm gonna help you reach that summit.

35:22.915 --> 35:25.542
In 10 days, you will leave here,

35:25.542 --> 35:28.212
you will not be the person
that you are now.

35:28.712 --> 35:32.341
You will leave Tranquillum House
and you will feel happier...

35:33.175 --> 35:34.176
healthier...

35:35.719 --> 35:36.970
lighter...

35:37.763 --> 35:38.680
freer.

35:39.598 --> 35:41.642
And on the last day of your stay,
you will come to me

35:41.642 --> 35:43.977
and you will say,
"Yes, Masha. Masha,

35:43.977 --> 35:46.563
"you were right!
I am not the same person.

35:46.563 --> 35:48.065
"I'm not the same person that I was.

35:48.065 --> 35:48.857
"I'm healed.

35:50.067 --> 35:51.318
"I am free.

35:51.318 --> 35:54.154
"Free of the negative habits

35:54.154 --> 35:57.574
"and chemicals and toxins and thoughts

35:57.574 --> 36:02.579
"that were holding me back.
My mind and my body are clear.

36:04.414 --> 36:09.294
And I am changed in ways
I could never have imagined."

36:09.294 --> 36:11.505
‐ Um, did you go through our bags?

36:11.505 --> 36:13.757
Because I seem to be missing a few things.

36:14.174 --> 36:17.052
‐ Yes. You are missing chocolate
and wine. As is Frances.

36:18.136 --> 36:21.181
‐ Well. And they're both antioxidants,

36:21.181 --> 36:22.432
so... [chuckles]

36:23.392 --> 36:25.185
TONY: Yeah, I'm missing stuff, too.

36:25.185 --> 36:26.937
You don't get to just steal our shit.

36:30.774 --> 36:34.695
‐ But you're mine now, Tony.
And you want to be mine.

36:36.446 --> 36:40.200
You want me to see you.
Peel you. Fix what I see.

36:41.201 --> 36:45.247
Tell me... does any
of this feel random to you?

36:48.250 --> 36:50.460
Answer me. Does it feel random?

36:54.590 --> 36:55.507
‐ No.

36:57.551 --> 37:00.095
[Carmel sobbing, sniffling]

37:00.387 --> 37:01.513
‐ Oh.

37:02.723 --> 37:04.057
What is it, huh?

37:04.057 --> 37:05.475
‐ I'm so happy.

37:07.477 --> 37:09.563
You are everything I hoped for.

37:10.689 --> 37:12.107
LARS: Oh, I'm sorry. But, um,

37:12.107 --> 37:14.193
you want us to just put ourselves

37:14.193 --> 37:15.736
in your hands, but...
[chuckles] ...we don't know

37:15.736 --> 37:18.363
the first thing about you.
I mean, what's your story?

37:21.158 --> 37:24.703
‐ My story is I died.

37:24.703 --> 37:27.080
♪

37:29.208 --> 37:31.585
I came here from Russia,
and I worked.

37:33.045 --> 37:35.756
And I worked
and I worked and I worked.

37:35.756 --> 37:36.882
I consumed.

37:36.882 --> 37:38.467
I climbed, I worked.

37:38.467 --> 37:39.968
I built a company.

37:39.968 --> 37:41.386
[echoing]
I worked. I consumed...

37:41.386 --> 37:43.013
I went over people.

37:43.013 --> 37:44.306
I went through people.

37:45.015 --> 37:46.016
And then...

37:47.476 --> 37:48.852
[gunshot]

37:48.852 --> 37:51.146
I was shot dead!

37:51.605 --> 37:52.856
In a parking garage.

37:52.856 --> 37:55.400
I was clinically dead.

37:59.821 --> 38:04.451
And that man, he brought me back to life.

38:06.286 --> 38:09.164
He cut into my chest,
he reached inside me.

38:09.164 --> 38:11.333
Just as I will reach inside all of you!

38:13.502 --> 38:14.837
Metaphorically.

38:15.921 --> 38:20.217
You have all come here to die.

38:21.301 --> 38:22.970
And I will bring you back.

38:26.473 --> 38:28.851
There can be birth in death.

38:30.060 --> 38:31.353
Tragedy...

38:33.188 --> 38:34.439
can be a blessing.

38:36.400 --> 38:38.610
I know, I was a corporate CEO

38:38.610 --> 38:39.945
and then boom!
[gunshot]

38:41.238 --> 38:43.282
♪ somber music playing ♪

38:45.659 --> 38:47.536
I was a little girl.

38:47.536 --> 38:49.788
And I was riding my bicycle.

38:51.164 --> 38:53.834
Reconnecting with joy

38:53.834 --> 38:56.086
and innocence.
‐ Excuse me!

38:57.337 --> 38:58.714
This is not appropriate.

38:59.006 --> 39:00.841
‐ I will decide what is appropriate.

39:01.425 --> 39:02.926
‐ You know our story.

39:05.137 --> 39:07.264
‐ Death will not be your story.

39:07.931 --> 39:09.808
HEATHER: Zoe.
‐ [panting] I'm sorry.

39:09.808 --> 39:10.934
‐ Oh, honey.

39:11.226 --> 39:13.145
[crying]

39:13.604 --> 39:16.398
NAPOLEON: She's okay.
HEATHER: No, she's not okay.

39:16.815 --> 39:18.525
What is wrong with you?

39:18.525 --> 39:20.402
‐ Step to the center, please, Heather.

39:22.654 --> 39:23.697
Step to the center.

39:31.288 --> 39:33.457
I prefer you not upset the group.

39:35.167 --> 39:37.669
‐ You prefer I not upset the group?

39:37.669 --> 39:39.922
‐ I prefer you not upset the group.

39:39.922 --> 39:41.965
‐ We came here for a retreat.

39:41.965 --> 39:43.258
To escape.

39:43.258 --> 39:46.053
‐ None of you shall retreat.
You will not escape.

39:46.053 --> 39:48.305
‐ You know why we're here.

39:48.305 --> 39:50.224
Do you really mean
to fuck with us like this?

39:50.224 --> 39:51.850
‐ Lapochka.

39:53.268 --> 39:55.103
This is Tranquillum.

39:57.397 --> 40:00.275
I mean to fuck with all of you.

40:00.275 --> 40:02.778
